race.comment: DISCO KICKS (4) is racing in good order, just missing at Toodyay two starts ago before a 1.1L defeat last start when being slowly away from the gates. Those two efforts stack up highly here with Valas replacing the apprentice hoop. Looks well placed in this event and can land the knockout blow. SOARING SOLO (3) showed good early speed and raced on the pace last start before fading to finish sixth, beaten 9 lengths, over 1190m at Moora. Sure to be prominent from the outset. SCHNOOTS (2) is racing in top order, winning as favourite at Mt Magnet last time out and looks well placed from the barrier again. Can put herself on the speed and give her rivals something to chase. ALBERT (5) turned in a moderate run over this journey last time out, settling in a rearward position and failing to make an impact when ninth over 1400m at Bunbury. Can bounce back. ROYALZEL (1) turned things around to get the job done by a nose over 1500m at Moora. Can go on with it.
